FINAL - Elkhorn North 5, @FmtNEBaseball 4. 
First State Bankâ€™s season ends in a nine inning battle. 
They went 24-10 and won a district championship.
First State Bank is down to its final three outs, again, after Elkhorn North plates one in the top of the ninth, 5-4.
Elkhorn North regains the lead on a sacrifice fly to left, 5-4, one out.
The ninth started with a HBP and a ball on Dix.

To the ninth we go. 
Ryan Dix will take over on the bump.

Colin Ridder ties the game with a sac fly to right. 4-4. 
A ninth might be in the cards.
Sintek has stolen second and third.
Sintek starts the bottom of the eighth with a single to left.

Winter limits the damage to one run, throwing eight frames, scattering 12 hits. 
He leaves to an ovation from the FSB fans. 
Post 20 has 3 outs to extend their season.
Elkhorn North retakes the lead with a bases loaded fielderâ€™s choice. 4-3.
Two First State Bank defensive miscues put runners on first and second for Elkhorn North.
Winter returns for the eighth. He has 10 pitches until the limit. https://t.co/dBsyUL8CK5

First State Bank goes down in order. 
To the eighth we go.

Winter hangs his fifth consecutive scoreless frame. 
Fremont will have a chance to win it in the bottom of the seventh.
Cortes cuts down a runner at home on a ground ball to third. Two away now.
Elkhorn North has put runners on second and third with one out in the top of the seventh.

Ridder scores on a wild pitch. 
The game is tied, 3-3.

Landon Mueller wears a pitch to start the sixth then is moved to second with a bunt. 
Colin Ridder enters the game and promptly steals third.
Winter nets a 1-2-3 inning on four pitches in the sixth.

First State Bank leaves a runner on second in the fifth. 
Onto the sixth with no change in the score, 3-2 Elkhorn North.
Winter has settled in now, putting up his third scoreless frame.
End of four - Elkhorn North 3, First State Bank 2.
Winter escapes the fourth unscathed after giving up back-to-back singles.
First State Bank scores a pair in the bottom of the third to cut the deficit to a run, 3-2.

Jackson Cyza grounds into a fielder's choice, plating a run. 
3-2, Elkhorn North.
Carter Sintek singles through the left side of the infield to put runners on the corners.

Cortes scores on a passed ball as Cal Janke works a walk.
3-1, bottom three.
Julius Cortes lifts a one-out double in the bottom of the third.
Winter hangs a zero in the third.
End of two - Elkhorn North 3, First State Bank 0.
Elkhorn North adds two runs in the second and leads 3-0.

First State Bank leaves a pair aboard in the bottom of the first. 
1-0 Elkhorn North going into the second.
Elkhorn North draws first blood with a two-out double, 1-0 top of the first.

Fremontâ€™s catcher is headed down to Hutch to continue his baseball career. 
The last Tiger to do that turned out pretty good. https://t.co/hAObUoTBHH
4 p.m. first pitch

First State Bank will face Elkhorn North tomorrow.

He struck out 10 in what is more than likely his final high school pitching performance.

Fremont's scoring threat in the third is ended by a pick-off at second base. 
It's 4-2 going into the fourth.
1-2-3 top of the third for the FSB defense capped by some snazzy leatherwork by Jackson Cyza at short.

Cal Janke does it again. 
The FSB left fielder slices his second double of the day to push Fremont in front 4-2 as part of a two-out rally in the second.
Sintek escapes a bases loaded jam in the top of the second with a strikeout, finishing off a three K frame.

FINAL - Millard South 17, @FmtNEBaseball 4. 
Post 20 will put their season on the line Monday night against Bellevue West. 
First pitch is set for 4 p.m.
Mueller beats out an infield single with the bases loaded to score a run. 17-4 now.
Colin Ridder nets a pinch hit single in the top of the fifth.

Winter gets a weak line drive out of Kozeal then induces a double play to end the fourth. 
First State Bank needs five runs to play the sixth, down 17-3.
Ryan Winter is on to eat up the rest of this one, relieving Ortiz with no outs in the fourth.
Millard South is up to 16 runs now in the bottom of the fourth.
First State Bank goes down in order in the fourth, aided by a runner getting thrown out at second.
End of three - Millard South 11, First State Bank 3.

Cam Kozeal hits a two run bomb, 11-3 Millard South. 
I kinda get why the SEC came calling.
Cooper Weitzel shows off the arm strength, gunning a runner at second after trying to take two on a FSB error.
Jackson Cyza buys a single with a ground ball that pops up off the third base bag. Donâ€™t see that every day.
The second ends but only after Millard South puts up six runs and now leads 9-3.
The 52â€™s add two more with a bloop single to right. 8-3, bottom two.
A sharp single down the left field line returns Millard Southâ€™s lead to three, 6-3.
Jariel Ortiz will come on in relief of Brandt Phillips with no outs and bases loaded in the bottom of the second.
A bases loaded passed ball puts Millard South in front 4-3, bottom two.
First State Bank answers Millard Southâ€™s 3 runs with three of their own in the top of the second.
Jax Sorensen ties the game at three with a single up the middle.
